The '''Bosavi languages''' are a [[language family|family]] of the [[Trans‚ÄìNew Guinea languages]] in the classification of [[Malcolm Ross (linguist)|Malcolm Ross]].

The languages, which are closely related (though they may have only 10‚Äì15% of their vocabulary in common), are:
*Bosavi Watershed: [[Kaluli language|Kaluli]]‚Äì[[Sonia language|Sonia]], [[Aimele language|Aimele]] (Kware), [[Kasua language|Kasua]]
*[[Onobasulu language|Onobasulu]]
*[[Edolo language|Edolo]]‚Äì[[Beami language|Beami]]
*[[Dibiyaso language|Dibiyaso]]

They are named after [[Mount Bosavi]]. Pronouns are:

