The '''Chinese in Algeria''' are [[Overseas Chinese|a group of Chinese nationals]] numbering an estimated 40,000 people residing in [[Algeria]].<ref name="wikileaks" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldometers.info/world-population/algeria-population/|title=Algeria Population (2017) - Worldometers|website=www.worldometers.info|language=en|access-date=2017-01-21}}</ref>  The recent migration of Chinese to Algeria is driven by commerce with most Chinese nationals working on infrastructure projects.<ref name="wikileaks" />

Tensions between Chinese merchants and locals in Algiers flared up in August 2009 when there was a clash in the Algiers suburb of [[Bab Ezzouar]], sparked by a confrontation between a migrant and a shop owner that drew in 100 people.<ref>{{Citation 
 | title = Chinese migrants in Algiers clash | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/8184499.stm| accessdate = 2009-08-11  | work=BBC News | date=2009-08-04}}</ref> A non-identified group of assailants attacked a Chinese owned company in Annaba in October 2016.

